#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Sagāthāvagga"
msgstr "1. With Verses"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Pātālasutta"
msgstr "4. The Abyss"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.4:1.1"
msgid "“Assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano yaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, when an uneducated ordinary person says that"

# BB translates as “bottomless abyss”, which overlooks the connotation with an underworld, found both in the commentary and the sanskrit. http://sanskritdictionary.com/?iencoding=iast&q=p%C4%81t%C4%81la&lang=sans&action=Search
msgctxt "sn36.4:1.2"
msgid "‘atthi mahāsamudde pātālo’ti."
msgstr "there’s a hellish abyss under the ocean,"

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.3"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano asantaṃ avijjamānaṃ evaṃ "
"vācaṃ bhāsati:"
msgstr "they’re speaking of something that doesn’t exist."

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.4"
msgid "‘atthi mahāsamudde pātālo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.5"
msgid ""
"Sārīrikānaṃ kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhānaṃ vedanānaṃ adhivacanaṃ yadidaṃ "
"‘pātālo’ti."
msgstr "‘Hellish abyss’ is a term for painful physical feelings."

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.6"
msgid ""
"Assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano sārīrikāya dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno "
"socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"When an uneducated ordinary person experiences painful physical feelings "
"they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into "
"confusion."

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.7"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘assutavā puthujjano pātāle na paccuṭṭhāsi, "
"gādhañca nājjhagā’."
msgstr ""
"They’re called an uneducated ordinary person who hasn’t stood up in the "
"hellish abyss and has gained no footing."

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.8"
msgid ""
"Sutavā ca kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sārīrikāya dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho "
"samāno neva socati, na kilamati, na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na "
"sammohaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"When an educated noble disciple experiences painful physical feelings they "
"don’t sorrow or pine or lament, beating their breast and falling into "
"confusion."

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.9"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘sutavā ariyasāvako pātāle paccuṭṭhāsi, gādhañca "
"ajjhagā’ti."
msgstr ""
"They’re called an educated noble disciple who has stood up in the hellish "
"abyss and gained a footing."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.4:2.1"
msgid "Yo etā nādhivāseti,"
msgstr "If you can’t abide"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:2.2"
msgid "uppannā vedanā dukhā;"
msgstr "those painful physical feelings"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:2.3"
msgid "Sārīrikā pāṇaharā,"
msgstr "that arise and sap your vitality;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:2.4"
msgid "yāhi phuṭṭho pavedhati."
msgstr "if you tremble at their touch,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.4:3.1"
msgid "Akkandati parodati,"
msgstr "weeping and wailing,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:3.2"
msgid "dubbalo appathāmako;"
msgstr "a weakling lacking strength—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:3.3"
msgid "Na so pātāle paccuṭṭhāsi,"
msgstr "you won’t stand up in the hellish abyss"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:3.4"
msgid "atho gādhampi nājjhagā."
msgstr "and gain a footing."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.207"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.1"
msgid "Yo cetā adhivāseti,"
msgstr "If you can abide"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.2"
msgid "uppannā vedanā dukhā;"
msgstr "those painful physical feelings"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.3"
msgid "Sārīrikā pāṇaharā,"
msgstr "that arise and sap your vitality;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.4"
msgid "yāhi phuṭṭho na vedhati;"
msgstr "if you don’t tremble at their touch—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.5"
msgid "Sa ve pātāle paccuṭṭhāsi,"
msgstr "you stand up in the hellish abyss"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.6"
msgid "atho gādhampi ajjhagā”ti."
msgstr "and gain a footing.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.7"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
